  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (in the UK)\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n- Record keeping\n- Risk assessment\n- Transaction monitoring\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Securities regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Risk-based approach\n- Regular audits\n- Staff training\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\n7. Emerging Considerations\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Cross-border enforcement collaboration\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
